  <prompt>Create the ApprovedSenderValidator service that validates fromMailbox values against the configured approved senders list. Phase 1 reads from CommunicationOptions only; Phase 2 will add Dataverse merge.</prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform developer expert in .NET 8 configuration binding, validation services, and ProblemDetails error handling</role>

  <goal>ApprovedSenderValidator validates fromMailbox against CommunicationOptions.ApprovedSenders[], returns the default sender when fromMailbox is null, and returns a typed INVALID_SENDER error when validation fails.</goal>

  <context>
    <background>The Communication Service needs to ensure only approved email addresses are used as senders. In Phase 1, the approved list comes from BFF configuration (appsettings.json). In Phase 2 (task 013), this will be extended to merge with Dataverse sprk_approvedsender records. This service is injected into CommunicationService for sender resolution before every Graph sendMail call.</background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/Errors/ProblemDetailsHelper.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Nodes/SendEmailNodeExecutor.cs</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">Register as concrete type: services.AddSingleton&lt;ApprovedSenderValidator&gt;(). No interface needed.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">Return ProblemDetails with errorCode INVALID_SENDER when validation fails.</constraint>
    <constraint source="Design">Any authenticated user can specify fromMailbox. Validation is against approved list, not user identity.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file path=".claude/constraints/api.md" reason="BFF service implementation rules"/>
      <file path=".claude/constraints/auth.md" reason="Authorization seam patterns"/>
      <file path=".claude/patterns/api/error-handling.md" reason="ProblemDetails error pattern with errorCode"/>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read .claude/patterns/api/error-handling.md for ProblemDetails pattern.</step>
    <step order="2">Create ApprovedSenderValidator class that takes IOptions&lt;CommunicationOptions&gt; via constructor injection.</step>
    <step order="3">Implement ResolveAsync(string? fromMailbox) method that: (a) if fromMailbox is null, returns the default sender from config (IsDefault=true), (b) if fromMailbox matches an approved sender (case-insensitive), returns that sender's email, (c) if fromMailbox does not match, returns a validation failure result.</step>
    <step order="4">Create ApprovedSenderResult record with IsValid (bool), Email (string), DisplayName (string), ErrorCode (string?), ErrorDetail (string?) properties.</step>
    <step order="5">Define error codes: INVALID_SENDER (fromMailbox not in approved list), NO_DEFAULT_SENDER (no default configured and fromMailbox is null).</step>
    <step order="6">Add XML documentation explaining Phase 1 behavior and Phase 2 extensibility.</step>
    <step order="7">Verify compilation with dotnet build.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Read error handling patterns and existing validators</tool>
    <tool name="Write">Create ApprovedSenderValidator and result types</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">Run dotnet build to verify compilation</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Communication/ApprovedSenderValidator.cs</output>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Communication/Models/ApprovedSenderResult.cs</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">ResolveAsync(null) returns the default sender when one is configured with IsDefault=true.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">ResolveAsync("valid@example.com") returns IsValid=true when email is in ApprovedSenders list.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">ResolveAsync("unknown@example.com") returns IsValid=false with ErrorCode=INVALID_SENDER.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Email comparison is case-insensitive.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">ResolveAsync(null) returns ErrorCode=NO_DEFAULT_SENDER when no default is configured.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">dotnet build completes without errors.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <execution>
    <skill>.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md</skill>
    <protocol>Load all knowledge files before starting. Design for Phase 2 extensibility.</protocol>
  </execution>
</task>
